=== radiPanel: Requests Toggle ===
Contributors: Matthew Gall (iCame)

radiPanel: Requests Toggle is an extension of the PHP / MySQL powered radiPanel system developed by Josh under a Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 2.0 UK: England & Wales Licence (which can be viewed at http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.0/uk/), that allows a user of the panel to enable / disable the request line feature of radiPanel at will via one simple button!

== Licence ==
radiPanel: Requests Toggle is licenced under a Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 2.0 UK: England & Wales Licence, terms of which can be viewed at http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.0/uk/ 

== Installation ==
Installation of radiPanel: Requests Toggle couldn't be more simple! Just follow these really easy steps!

1) Extract the .zip file you downloaded (If you're reading this, then you probably have done this)
2) Upload all files contained in this file to their respective locations on your system. For reference the following files are modified:

(*) _frontend/requests.php
(*) _res/radio/requests.php
(+) _inc/requests.status

Symbols:
(+) Files added in this released
(*) Files modified in this release
(-) Files removed in this release
 
3) Enjoy!

